HEADWORD: genotype
<hw>gen"o*type</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Genetics)</fld> <def>A group of
organisms sharing a specific genetic constitution.</def>
<wns>[wns=1]</wns>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Genetics)</fld> <def>The genetic constitution of an
organism, specifying the particular alleles at defined loci in the
genome; -- used with respect to one gene, a specific group of genes, or
the entire set of genes within the organism. Contrasted with
<contr>phenotype</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> genetic constitution.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> + <source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>genotypical</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>genotypic</ent>⟦br⟧
